1
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,160
Why is there still no power?

2
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:47,280
Don't you know?

3
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:51,360
The concession is repairing the power lines these days.

4
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:55,160
Ordinary households have been experiencing intermittent power outages.

5
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,720
Sometimes the streetlights and neon lights

6
00:01:58,240 --> 00:01:59,840
can suddenly go out halfway.

7
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,690
Only in the Tian Mansion

8
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,200
can it be brightly lit every day.

9
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:29,680
Shanghai is also almost becoming a dark world.

10
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,520
Yujiao,

11
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,040
have you thought about going to Chongqing?

12
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,560
With you?

13
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:10,040
I was thinking, where should I go?

14
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,840
Going to Hong Kong to be a gentry in exile

15
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,560
is really too boring.

16
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,880
Europe

17
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,730
has also started fighting.

18
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:25,120
Otherwise, let's go to Switzerland

19
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,480
and be a lonely wanderer.

20
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:30,680
Who knows?

21
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,680
Have you ever thought about

22
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,240
when Don Quixote challenged the windmills,

23
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,840
did he know what he was doing?

24
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,960
How did that quote describe him?

25
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,480
A sane Don Quixote

26
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,880
is of little use.

27
00:03:56,040 --> 00:04:00,000
A crazy one is infinitely interesting.

28
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,040
To be unkind,

29
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,280
I would rather

30
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:09,280
Don Quixote stay crazy forever.

31
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:20,000
Master,

32
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:22,360
our dedicated power supply line is broken.

33
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,690
Maintenance personnel will be here soon.

34
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,080
I'll go watch them.

35
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:37,320
After Wanfu finishes shipping the last batch of goods,

36
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,960
your family will leave.

37
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,290
It should be before the Mid-Autumn Festival.

38
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:46,480
You should also discuss where to go.

39
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,720
We will accompany you to the end.

40
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,159
We won't leave first.

41
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:59,080
In a mediocre and real place,

42
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:02,120
doing heroic and illusory things.

43
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,330
Do you think you are Crazy Don Quixote?

44
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,880
My match factory is very profitable.

45
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,970
Many people rush for it as soon as I want to sell it.

46
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,280
It sold for a very good price.

47
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,160
Besides the money I have to give Orlando,

48
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,480
there is still a large sum left.

49
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:29,280
You don't need to worry about me.

50
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,920
Master, I'm leaving.

51
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,120
Chief.

52
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,780
Chief, urgent telegram from headquarters.

53
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,240
Master,

54
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:29,680
the Japanese suddenly broke into our machinery factory.

55
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,210
How many machines are left?

56
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:31,920
The last crate.

57
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:34,000
It was moved into the concession last night.

58
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,860
The last crate.

59
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:35,800
The last crate.

60
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,220
It's all empty.

61
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,560
It's all empty.

62
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,720
Good job, Wanfu.

63
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,680
Master,

64
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,440
the Japanese definitely won't let us off.

65
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,040
We need to find a way to leave.

66
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,159
Go where?

67
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,640
Hello?

68
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,520
Speaking.

69
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,320
Got it.

70
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,520
Huang Ziming,

71
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,360
is he the Huang you mentioned?

72
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,560
Yes.

73
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,080
As soon as we received intel about the machinery factory,

74
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,840
we made this arrangement immediately.

75
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,840
Today? Do we need to evacuate now?

76
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,200
Yes, right now.

77
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:36,919
Mr. Tian,

78
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,400
take a car to the Cathay Hotel on Nanjing Road.

79
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,400
Someone will pick you up at the back door.

80
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,120
From there, go to Shiliupu Dock.

81
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,800
I'll explain the details on the way.

82
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,800
Blindy, how many people do you have?

83
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,320
Besides me, there are a few other helpers.

84
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,400
But Mr. Tian, don't alert anyone now.

85
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,680
Let's go first.

86
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,920
Mr. Huang,

87
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,880
if I leave,

88
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,360
what about Wanfu and the others?

89
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,570
We will send you away first.

90
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,520
On behalf of the NBIS Shanghai Station,

91
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,520
I guarantee the safety of everyone in the Tian family.

92
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,320
Now?

93
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:24,680
Can I take all my cameras with me?

94
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,720
Master.

95
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,960
Kudo has come with Furukawa,

96
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,640
followed by many Japanese plainclothes officers.

97
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,970
Our front and back doors

98
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,210
are all surrounded.

99
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:28,480
Toyotomi Hideyoshi has a famous saying.

100
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,840
If the cuckoo doesn't sing, I'll make it sing.

101
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,720
I know what a cuckoo is.

102
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:38,520
But what kind of bird is Toyotomi Hideyoshi?

103
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,840
You bastard,

104
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:40,960
what did you say?

105
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,620
This person is very impolite.

106
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,280
Can you ask him to leave first?

107
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,320
Mr. Tian, he is a soldier.

108
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,840
He doesn't understand social etiquette.

109
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:51,120
Let's get back to the main point.

110
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,280
You failed me and deceived me.

111
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:57,440
You also deceived the Imperial Japanese Army.

112
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:00,360
You put me in an extremely difficult position.

113
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,840
This is also the best situation

114
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,320
I could fight for you.

115
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:08,560
If it weren't for my bitter persuasion,

116
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,400
they would have directly arrested you and sent you to the Gendarmerie

117
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,130
under the name of being an anti-Japanese element

118
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,960
and destroying Shanghai's economy.

119
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,880
I'm a respectable figure

120
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,120
in the French Concession.

121
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:22,400
Is it that easy

122
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,080
to just arrest me so casually?

123
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,400
Stop saying silly things.

124
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,760
So what?

125
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:30,680
Everyone is the same to us.

126
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,560
Mr. Tian,

127
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:36,320
dismantling and moving away the entire Tailai Machinery Factory

128
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,960
is not only a breach of faith,

129
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,560
but also a serious crime.

130
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,440
We also have hard evidence

131
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,520
proving that half a year ago,

132
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:50,160
you shielded a Communist anti-Japanese fighter.

133
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,840
The military has decided

134
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:55,200
to take over all the Tian Group businesses in the Chinese-administered area.

135
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,960
You must turn over a new leaf.

136
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,400
This is your last chance.

137
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,160
Sign it.

138
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,840
Kudo.

139
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,370
I'm your classmate.

140
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,840
You know me.

141
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:14,160
Wearing a uniform and carrying a saber

142
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,100
to coerce me like this,

143
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,610
is hard for me to accept.

144
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,400
I know your personality.

145
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,610
You were dissatisfied with me,

146
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,740
so you played a trick on me.

147
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:29,320
But you never intended to ruin

148
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:33,760
Sino-Japanese good neighborliness and friendship and economic cooperation, right?

149
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:36,160
Now that you've taken your revenge on me,

150
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,960
no more joking.

151
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,640
Mr. Furukawa is not only doing me a favor,

152
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:45,250
he also genuinely thinks you're a financial talent.

153
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,080
That's why he held back

154
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,410
those radicals at Army Headquarters.

155
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,920
They won't do anything to you for now.

156
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:56,240
So, you must seize the opportunity,

157
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,880
show your sincerity,

158
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,640
and actively join us.

159
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,200
Bring all your funds and assets

160
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,090
from the concession in.

161
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,400
Believe me.

162
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:09,360
A controlled economy has its own charm.

163
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,080
Together, we will

164
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:14,720
make the Central China Light Industry Association bigger and stronger.

165
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:17,680
These unpleasantries will soon pass.

166
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,120
We must look to the future.

167
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,210
There is no other possibility.

168
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:25,360
A controlled economy has its own charm.

169
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:30,240
Aren't you painting the Development Company and the controlled economy

170
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,640
in too good a light?

171
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,960
As far as I know,

172
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:37,340
Japanese consortiums are no longer willing to invest.

173
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:41,380
It's because they think the military interferes too much,

174
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:44,560
and the war never ends.

175
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,260
Why would I want to invest money in it?

176
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:53,040
If I take this position today,

177
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,580
in the eyes of the Chinese,

178
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,100
I'm not just a traitor.

179
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,560
I still have to keep putting money into it.

180
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,890
I've already lost a lot.

181
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,850
My family property is almost all sold off.

182
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,440
The reason I did that before

183
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:08,740
was because I didn't want my family wealth to be completely depleted.

184
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,730
What exactly are you trying to say?

185
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:15,720
I want to say,

186
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,090
I just want to be a businessman.

187
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,720
Let me go to Europe via Hong Kong.

188
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,560
Let me live.

189
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:27,360
No, absolutely not.

190
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,600
Tian Jiatai.

191
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:29,680
What you have done

192
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,210
shows you are no longer a simple businessman.

193
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,640
If you don't sign,

194
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,800
we will throw you in prison.

195
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:38,600
We cannot guarantee your life or death.

196
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:51,800
Okay.

197
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,200
Give me a day to think about it.

198
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,120
Absolutely not.

199
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:05,920
Kudo,

200
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,520
we are classmates.

201
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,200
I am Chinese.

202
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,800
For me to do these things,

203
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:14,680
I also need time to adjust.

204
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:19,200
Besides, today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

205
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:20,620
I checked the almanac.

206
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,280
Other than admiring the moon and eating mooncakes,

207
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,560
it's inauspicious to do anything else.

208
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:26,020
Can you make an exception?

209
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,880
To the Chinese,

210
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:34,280
the Mid-Autumn Festival is very important.

211
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,280
Can you give him some time?

212
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,890
I'll give you an hour to think about it.

213
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,720
We'll wait outside.

214
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:43,480
If we don't get your signature today,

215
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:46,100
we won't withdraw the Gendarmerie outside.

216
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,860
I guarantee not even a bird

217
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:50,040
can fly in or out.

218
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,280
Tian.

219
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:00,600
What's the difference between signing in an hour

220
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,200
and signing now?

221
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,840
This is someone else's house.

222
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,120
Be careful.

223
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:13,720
Yes.

224
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:27,280
When you break something in someone else's house,

225
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:29,600
the least you can do is apologize.

226
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,800
I'm sorry, Mr. Tian.

227
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,080
Mr. Kakutani was too careless.

228
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,040
The one who broke it should apologize.

229
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,280
Mr. Furukawa.

230
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:56,800
I will never apologize to this Chinese.

231
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,120
Bastard!

232
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,130
Have you forgotten who you are?

233
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,760
I know you are proud,

234
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,579
so I've always yielded to you.

235
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,280
Not because I like you,

236
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,560
but because accommodating you makes getting things done

237
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:12,640
cheaper.

238
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,480
But you also need to be sensible.

239
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:16,000
Whose home is this?

240
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,760
Whose land is this?

241
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,319
Open your eyes and look carefully.

242
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,160
Don't let pride blind you.

243
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,599
Don't you think

244
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,119
it's ridiculous for prey to talk about dignity

245
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,760
with a hunter?

246
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,480
What's important now is obedience.

247
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,000
Yes.

248
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,200
Mr. Tian, the Development Company will compensate you

249
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,440
for the vase later.

250
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,400
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

251
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:19,240
Miss Xiaoyue.

252
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,160
Here, for your squad.

253
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,160
Okay, thank you.

254
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,820
We even have mooncakes to eat.

255
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,880
Here, for our medical team.

256
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,440
Okay.

257
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,640
Here, for your squad.

258
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:40,560
Okay.

259
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:46,770
Have a mooncake.

260
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,100
It's Mid-Autumn Festival again.

261
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,930
Does everyone have one?

262
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:53,840
Yes.

263
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,720
Thank you.

264
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,850
What are you staring at?

265
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:15,720
I was just thinking of that Mid-Autumn Festival on the Shanghai Battlefield.

266
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:17,520
Do you remember I told you before

267
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,840
that someone used water caltrops as mooncake stuffing?

268
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,200
That was my orderly,

269
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:23,400
Kong Erbao.

270
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,480
The kid didn't know how to tie puttees.

271
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:27,360
I helped him tie them that night.

272
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:30,520
After that, we took the mooncakes into the trenches

273
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,680
and looked at the moon with the soldiers.

274
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:36,480
Everyone sang a little tune from their hometown.

275
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:39,160
Finally, we sang 'The River All Red' together.

276
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:40,920
Together.

277
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,360
Now they are all gone.

278
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,920
That night was very similar to today.

279
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,320
It was also before a big battle.

280
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:53,280
Very peaceful, yet very restless.

281
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,500
But the only difference is

282
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,460
that there is no moon tonight.

283
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,380
It will probably rain later tonight.

284
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:08,960
Rain on Mid-Autumn Day means a harsh winter.

285
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:14,280
The older generation says that if it rains on Mid-Autumn Festival,

286
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:16,480
there will likely be a spring drought the following year.

287
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,680
As if the disaster of war wasn't enough,

288
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:20,650
there are also natural disasters.

289
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,760
God really doesn't want people to live.

290
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:25,960
I think the rain is good.

291
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,290
The heavier the better.

292
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,160
Why?

293
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,200
Wind and rain are another kind of night.

294
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,480
It can make the enemy blind

295
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,080
and deaf.

296
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,240
As for us,

297
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,080
we know the terrain

298
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,840
as well as our own backyard.

299
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,000
This is a great psychological advantage.

300
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,600
Sparrow warfare and mobile warfare

301
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,240
are actually also psychological warfare.

302
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,200
Even though we are few in number,

303
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:43,920
but

304
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,450
the wind and rain will build our momentum.

305
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,040
It will plunge the Japanese

306
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,640
into unknown fear.

307
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:51,040
Commander Zhang,

308
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,920
the signal for the Advance Column has sounded.

309
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,840
Tell everyone to get ready to move out.

310
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:56,560
Yes.

311
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,800
What is the secret of guerrilla warfare you taught me?

312
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,860
Fight if you can win, run if you can't.

313
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:10,880
Then remember,

314
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,920
fight if you can win, run if you can't.

315
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,160
Run back.

316
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:10,380
Father, stop looking.

317
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,040
The clouds are so thick,

318
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:13,900
the moon probably won't come out.

319
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:16,040
It might even rain.

320
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:19,400
I want to ride the wind and ask the Creator.

321
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:23,280
The road is hard to pass, and letters are hard to send.

322
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:29,900
The hall is filled with nothing but the red glow of candles.

323
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:34,160
Drink with ease, sing with ease.

324
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:38,120
Madam,

325
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:39,290
you're back.

326
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:40,360
Wanfu,

327
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:41,880
where is Mr. Tian?

328
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:42,880
Isn't he coming over

329
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,210
to spend the Mid-Autumn Festival with us?

330
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,400
Mr. Tian is seeing guests in the main building.

331
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:58,360
Blind Huang came.

332
00:22:58,600 --> 00:22:59,440
He was supposed to take Mr. Tian

333
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,960
to Chongqing tonight.

334
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,520
But a large group of Japanese arrived.

335
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,720
Now they've surrounded

336
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,120
the entire Tian Mansion.

337
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:09,220
Blind Huang and his men are also trapped inside.

338
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,920
Sir, why did you come over?

339
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:24,720
I promised Master

340
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,320
to spend the Mid-Autumn Festival together,

341
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:27,360
so I had to come.

342
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,640
What about the Japanese?

343
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:31,640
Mr. Tian,

344
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,720
come here.

345
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:33,840
Take a seat.

346
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,960
I've prepared a pot of old wine and some dishes.

347
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,240
Let's spend the Mid-Autumn Festival together.

348
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:43,480
Okay.

349
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,610
We'll admire the moon together later.

350
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,160
Okay.

351
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:50,120
It's a pity, I see these clouds today

352
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,280
just won't clear up.

353
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:54,440
I'm afraid the moon won't come out tonight.

354
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,000
Let's make a bet.

355
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:58,800
The moon will definitely come out tonight.

356
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:00,960
Okay, I believe you.

357
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:02,280
Come, Master.

358
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,400
Come.

359
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,680
Mr. Tian,

360
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:13,240
have you heard any news

361
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:17,000
about the Jiangnan Anti-Japanese Volunteer Army recently?

362
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:19,380
I really haven't had the time.

363
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,560
Last time,

364
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:25,000
they blew up the railway tracks at Xushuguan.

365
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:28,760
This time at Hongqiao,

366
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:31,220
four Japanese Army planes were burned down.

367
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,040
Brave and resourceful.

368
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,000
This is where the national spirit lies.

369
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,530
Even in the core area controlled by the enemy,

370
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,880
they can effectively attack.

371
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,360
I increasingly feel that

372
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:44,080
our inevitable victory is not just empty talk.

373
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,680
I'd like to hear more.

374
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:48,320
Right now,

375
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:51,200
the Japanese can't advance,

376
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:53,360
and they are struggling to defend.

377
00:24:53,360 --> 00:24:54,880
They are bogged down.

378
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,840
As long as all Chinese men, women, and children

379
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,640
unite as one and grit our teeth to endure,

380
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:03,120
enduring for five, eight, or ten years,

381
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,330
the final victory will surely be ours.

382
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:07,920
Enduring.

383
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:11,040
Five, eight, ten years.

384
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:13,600
Master.

385
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,880
I have already endured for three years.

386
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:19,560
Do you think I can still endure it?

387
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,440
You can.

388
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:25,400
Every cloud has a silver lining.

389
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,920
But to endure,

390
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:32,120
one needs the capital to do so.

391
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:34,000
Why wouldn't you have the capital?

392
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,840
Being alive is the capital.

393
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:38,160
Good, well said.

394
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,170
Being alive is the capital.

395
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:43,400
Master, every time I come here,

396
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:44,840
I benefit a lot.

397
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,440
You flatter me.

398
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,600
Today,

399
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:50,320
we can consider we've spent the Mid-Autumn Festival together.

400
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,240
I still have things to do over there.

401
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:53,160
I'm afraid

402
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,720
I have to go back before the moon comes out.

403
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:56,240
What...

404
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,980
Come, after drinking this glass of wine,

405
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,530
I will take my leave.

406
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:01,980
This...

407
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:02,440
Come.

408
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,680
Come.

409
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:13,800
Alright.

410
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:17,520
Mr. Tian, the mooncake hasn't been eaten yet.

411
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:20,720
Right, have some mooncake.

412
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:25,880
Farewell, Master.

413
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,900
Father, let's go see Mr. Tian out.

414
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:36,920
Mr. Tian.

415
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:40,200
Master, what should we do?

416
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,020
We can't go to Chongqing anymore.

417
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:46,320
Then, do you have any plans?

418
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:48,320
What plans?

419
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,280
Be a traitor.

420
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,280
Before I came today,

421
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:56,360
I wanted to tell you something.

422
00:26:56,360 --> 00:26:57,760
Pack your things tonight

423
00:26:58,280 --> 00:27:00,280
and leave Tian Mansion as soon as possible.

424
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:01,810
Don't be in such disbelief.

425
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:05,880
It is human instinct to seek advantage and avoid harm.

426
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,690
The vast Tian family business,

427
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,500
founded by my brother with his life's blood,

428
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:12,920
cannot be completely ruined because of me.

429
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,040
Before,

430
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,560
I thought I was different from those who fell

431
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:18,020
and those who joined Wang.

432
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,880
I overestimated myself.

433
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:24,480
It's just the pot calling the kettle black.

434
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:28,040
Hurry up and pack your things.

435
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:29,170
Don't alert Master.

436
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:30,930
As soon as possible,

437
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,970
leave the home of a traitor.

438
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,080
Mr. Tian.

439
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,360
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

440
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,560
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

441
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:23,080
Mr. Tian, have you signed the papers?

442
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:25,520
Not yet.

443
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,320
I think for such an important ceremony,

444
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:31,000
it's best to sign it in front of you.

445
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:32,960
It's foolproof.

446
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:03,960
Here.

447
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,480
Here.

448
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:28,440
Here.

449
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:29,840
Here.

450
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:37,410
I suddenly remembered something.

451
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,080
What is it?

452
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,940
He didn't apologize to me.

453
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:42,810
Apologize for what?

454
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:44,920
He just broke my Kaffir lily.

455
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:46,480
He didn't apologize.

456
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,120
Didn't he already apologize

457
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:50,090
and promise to pay you back?

458
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:51,520
No.

459
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:54,800
He broke it,

460
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,450
so he should apologize.

461
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,960
You want Mr. Kakutani to apologize to you?

462
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,240
No.

463
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:04,380
I don't want him to apologize now.

464
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:05,520
Can I hit him?

465
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,400
Hit him?

466
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:09,420
Just for a Kaffir lily?

467
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:10,530
Is it necessary?

468
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,690
It is necessary.

469
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:13,160
Do you have to do this?

470
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,120
Yes.

471
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:16,360
I've grown that Kaffir lily for years.

472
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:18,520
He broke it and didn't apologize.

473
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,360
I just can't swallow my anger.

474
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,560
I want to hit him. I want to slap his face.

475
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,380
If you don't let me hit him,

476
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:26,020
then I won't sign this.

477
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,610
Mr. Tian, do you have to act like a child

478
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,320
just to vent your anger?

479
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:31,480
Yes.

480
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:39,600
We must complete our mission today.

481
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:42,080
Kakutani, this is a military order.

482
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:43,930
I'm counting on you.

483
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,240
Yes, sir.

484
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:48,800
Come stand here.

485
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:55,560
Attention.

486
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:23,160
Attention.

487
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:25,900
Stand up straight.

488
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:26,720
Tian!

489
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,000
Stand up straight.

490
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,720
Stand up straight.

491
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,000
Stand up straight.

492
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:34,080
I told you to stand up straight.

493
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:34,760
Tian!

494
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,800
Stop hitting him.

495
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:40,560
Tian Jiatai, are you playing with us?

496
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,320
You just realized that?

497
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:47,880
I am playing with you.

498
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:50,130
I told you to stand up straight.

499
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:52,520
You lunatic!

500
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:55,360
Tian, you will die if you do this.

501
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:00,200
Old classmate, let me tell you,

502
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:03,440
I never intended to sign it.

503
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,760
You are insulting me.

504
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:11,490
You are insulting the Imperial soldiers.

505
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:14,880
Go to hell!

506
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:15,920
Don't shoot!

507
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:16,720
Wait a minute.

508
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:22,000
So you know what insult is?

509
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:24,720
Shoot me.

510
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,600
Report to your superiors

511
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,010
that you were insulted.

512
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,720
A gentleman prefers death to humiliation.

513
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:45,040
Calm down.

514
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:48,280
You are not worthy of killing me.

515
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,320
Tian Jiatai!

516
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:07,800
Master!

517
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,360
Don't move.

518
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,840
Continue.

519
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,000
Sirs.

520
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,480
I know something.

521
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:16,440
Yesterday,

522
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,040
before the Japanese

523
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,080
arrived,

524
00:35:19,120 --> 00:35:21,400
there was a man among those who came in.

525
00:35:22,200 --> 00:35:25,240
I saw him in the backyard before.

526
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:28,820
He used to come specifically to visit Meng Wanfu's family.

527
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:30,440
What did he look like?

528
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:33,320
He... He had a scar here.

529
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:37,200
I've always thought there was something wrong with their family.

530
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:38,640
Think about it. He's a cook.

531
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:41,120
His wife reads to Mr. Tian.

532
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:44,280
His old man spouts pedantic terms all day.

533
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:46,300
Does he look like a cook's father?

534
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:49,040
And yet Mr. Tian thinks highly of him.

535
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:53,680
Later, Mr. Tian stopped letting him be a cook.

536
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,440
After Qi left,

537
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:57,240
he was promoted to be a follower.

538
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:59,080
He was sent running around everywhere,

539
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:00,320
supposedly doing business.

540
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:02,980
But I... I don't know what he was actually doing.

541
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:04,720
Before the incident,

542
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,400
Mr. Tian even made a special trip to the backyard

543
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:09,520
and spent the Mid-Autumn Festival with their family.

544
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:11,840
The man with a scar on his face that he mentioned

545
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:14,640
is Huang Ziming, Regimental Commander of the Anti-Japanese Traitor Elimination Group.

546
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:18,000
It seems that in the entire Tian Mansion,

547
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:20,600
only Meng Wanfu is in contact with Huang Ziming.

548
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,480
Does this mean Meng Wanfu

549
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:25,970
is from the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics?

550
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:28,520
Who is Huang Ziming?

551
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,960
Huang Ziming

552
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:34,840
was Zhang Yunkui's subordinate.

553
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:37,200
They shared a life-and-death bond.

554
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:38,460
What about Meng Wanfu?

555
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:39,960
Meng Wanfu

556
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:42,650
was also Zhang Yunkui's subordinate.

557
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:43,880
Who is Zhang Yunkui?

558
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:47,200
Brigade Commander, Major General of the 87th Brigade.

559
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:48,930
During the Battle of Shanghai,

560
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:52,880
he led his troops to annihilate thousands of Japanese invaders.

561
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:56,280
My son died a worthy death.

562
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:57,920
Who is your son?

563
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:59,760
Zhang Yunkui.

564
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,000
What about Meng Wanfu?

565
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,280
Meng Wanfu is my son.

566
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:13,920
Zhang Yunkui and Meng Wanfu are both my sons.

567
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:18,050
They are both patriotic men who fought in the war of resistance.

568
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,920
This crazy old man

569
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:23,200
says his son is Zhang Yunkui.

570
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,280
Is it possible

571
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,840
that Meng Wanfu is

572
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:28,760
Brigade Commander, Major General Zhang Yunkui?

573
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:29,840
Zhang Yunkui?

574
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:30,800
Yes.

575
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:33,360
The Major General who disobeyed military orders during the Battle of Shanghai

576
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,360
and whose whereabouts are unknown.

577
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:38,560
Meng Wanfu is close to Huang Ziming.

578
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,000
Huang Ziming's superior is Tieshu.

579
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:44,920
So Meng Wanfu is Zhang Yunkui,

580
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:48,280
and possibly Tieshu.

581
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:52,760
Next.

582
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,520
You must be Mrs. Meng.

583
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:00,320
Here's the thing.

584
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,200
This sword was found in your room.

585
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:03,860
Why do you have this sword?

586
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:09,000
Your husband Meng Wanfu was a soldier.

587
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,120
He's just a cook.

588
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,720
Meng Wanfu?

589
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,040
Meng Wanfu.

590
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,200
But your father just said

591
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:21,960
his son's name is Zhang Yunkui.

592
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:42,920
Madam, are you alright?

593
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:43,800
Are you okay?

594
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:44,920
I'm fine.

595
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:49,960
Weren't we supposed to be interrogated separately?

596
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:50,960
How did you get in?

597
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:59,120
Ma Jiangtian from the Gendarmerie

598
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,720
let me in on purpose.

599
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:03,560
He told me that for such a big case,

600
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:05,120
someone has to take the blame.

601
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:07,640
But since Huang Ziming ran away,

602
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:09,760
he held that sword and asked me

603
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:12,640
if I was Wanfu or Zhang Yunkui.

604
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:15,520
If you are Wanfu,

605
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:17,240
You won't survive.

606
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,440
But if you admit you are Yunkui,

607
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:22,840
you'll still be of value to them.

608
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,480
You might even live.

609
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:27,880
Why?

610
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,040
I haven't figured it out either,

611
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:31,960
but this is at least a chance.

612
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:35,380
I will tell you everything about Yunkui now.

613
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:37,520
Remember as much as you can.

614
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:41,800
Then play it by ear, okay?

615
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:02,760
It seems

616
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,520
my speculation is correct.

617
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,760
Meng Wanfu is Tieshu.

618
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:08,920
If Meng Wanfu is Tieshu,

619
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,760
everything that happened in the Tian Mansion

620
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:13,120
makes sense.

621
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:16,720
The Army Headquarters wanted to use Tian Jiatai,

622
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:19,360
and so did the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics.

623
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:19,760
Right.

624
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:23,400
Tieshu was completely safe hiding in the Tian Mansion.

625
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:26,560
Tian Jiatai followed Tieshu's orders

626
00:40:27,040 --> 00:40:29,880
to dismantle the machinery factory and ship it out of Shanghai.

627
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:32,080
But Furukawa found out and stopped him.

628
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,960
Tian Jiatai was caught in a dilemma

629
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,560
and chose to commit suicide.

630
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:37,720
Huang Ziming and his gang

631
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:40,760
shot Furukawa and fled.

632
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:43,360
But Meng Wanfu didn't leave with them.

633
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:45,720
It's because his father,

634
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:48,440
wife, and children are all in the Tian Mansion.

635
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:51,040
So he could only pretend to be a cook

636
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:52,600
to get away with it.

637
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:56,680
Makes sense.

638
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:03,580
The clue about Meng Wanfu is very important.

639
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,800
I need to take his family

640
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:08,180
back to the Hongkou Gendarmerie Command

641
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:09,880
for further interrogation.

642
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:13,400
I demand immediate extradition procedures.

643
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:14,720
I disagree.

644
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:17,140
This is against the rules.

645
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:20,440
A cook, an old man,

646
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:21,640
and a maid...

647
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:23,800
What do they have to do with the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics?

648
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:24,720
Mr. Oba.

649
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:27,320
Mr. Tian is from the French Concession.

650
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:29,640
A murder that occurred in the French Concession

651
00:41:29,640 --> 00:41:31,560
cannot be interrogated outside of it.

652
00:41:31,560 --> 00:41:35,600
Otherwise, the concession will lose all its face and dignity.

653
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:38,720
No. 76 Jessfield Road.

654
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:41,640
It's an extra-settlement road area.

655
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:43,400
If the interrogation takes place at the Secret Service Headquarters,

656
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:47,060
it wouldn't be considered leaving the French Concession, right?

657
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,680
That is a good compromise.

658
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:55,000
I think we should hand

659
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:57,560
this matter over to No. 76.

660
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:01,760
Let's do that.

661
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:05,840
All right. We'll take our leave.

662
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:14,000
I just received notice from Lieutenant Colonel Haruki.

663
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,640
You have been merged

664
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:17,800
into No. 76 Secret Service Headquarters.

665
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,440
Take this case with you.

666
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:20,800
Section Chief.

667
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:23,280
Wouldn't this case become theirs?

668
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:26,280
What about his wife?

669
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:28,200
Should we release his wife first

670
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:30,340
and see if she contacts Huang Ziming?

671
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:32,480
We'll play the long game.

672
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:35,240
Do as you see fit.

673
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,200
Come.

674
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:42,280
Also, come with me.

675
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:46,050
Why the long face when we just won a great victory?

676
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:49,200
Wang Jingwei is preparing to establish a puppet government.

677
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:51,160
I'm worried that the future situation of the War of Resistance

678
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,960
will become increasingly grim.

679
00:42:53,680 --> 00:42:55,840
When we were attacking the Japanese invaders at Sanhuang Village,

680
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:57,640
Ge Zhiyuan sent his intelligence team

681
00:42:57,640 --> 00:42:58,640
to attack us.

682
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Fortunately, we had enough people

683
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
and were prepared,

684
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,320
so they couldn't make a move.

685
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:04,000
Did he collude with the Japanese and puppets in advance?
